 at first used as a title of respect for male clergy of every rank, but in the Western Church it gradually came to be restricted to bishops, and then only to the bishop of Rome; in the Eastern Church it continued to be used of all priests (see   Popov  ,   Papas  ). The nickname would have been used for a vain or pompous man, or for someone who had played the part of the pope in a pageant or play. The surname is also present in Ireland and Scotland.","North German: variant of   Poppe  .","German: translation of   Pabst  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Popov","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Russian Nikolay, Oleg, Grigoriy, Anatoly, Andrei, Arkadi, Dmitriy, Mikhail, Sergey.  Bulgarian or Macedonian Atanas, Dimitar, Yordan.  Serbian Bosko, Bozidar, Branko.","Russian, Bulgarian, Macedonian, Serbian, and Rusyn: patronymic from <i>pop</i> ‘priest’, from Greek <i>pappas</i> ‘father’ (compare English   Pope  ). The name may sometimes derive from a nickname, but celibacy was not enjoined on priests of the Orthodox Church and so the name can indeed mean ‘son of the priest’. In many cases, however, the Russian name means no more than ‘of the priest’ and designates a servant of a priest. Compare   Popoff  , see also   Pop   2,   Popovic  , and   Popovski   1.","Jewish (American): most likely a shortened form of   Popovski   2. Compare   Popoff  ."]},{"name":"Papke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Bernhard, Erwin, Hans, Otto, Willi.","North German (also <b>Päpke</b>): nickname from a diminutive of Low German <i>pape</i>, Dutch <i>paepe</i> ‘pope’. Compare   Pope  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"wife John Pope I was born in 1345, in England, United Kingdom. She married John Pope I. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1345–":"1345–Surnud","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1345–":"1345–Kuollut","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1345–":"1345–Décédée","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–Décédée","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"wife John Pope I est née en 1345, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John Pope I. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1345–":"1345–Verstorben","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–Verstorben","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"England, United Kingdom","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England","lifeSummary":"wife John Pope I wurde 1345 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat John Pope I geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1345–":"1345–Desede","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–Desede","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"Angletè, United Kingdom","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England"},"hu":{"1345–":"1345–elhunyt","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1345–Female":"1345–elhunyt","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","England":"Anglia, United Kingdom","Twyford, Bu